    • ensureFamixPackage

      public Package ensureFamixPackage(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.IPackageBinding bnd, String name)
      Returns a Famix Namespace associated with its IPackageBinding and/or fully qualified name. The Entity is created if it does not exist (see also AbstractDictionary.ensureFamixPackage(Object, String)). Also creates or recovers recusively it's parent namespaces.
      At least one of bnd and name must be non null.
      Parameters:
      bnd - -- the JDT Binding that may be used as a uniq key to recover this namespace
      name - -- fully qualified name of the namespace (e.g. 'java.lang')
      Returns:
      the Famix Namespace found or created. May return null in case of a Famix error

      Adds location information to a Famix Entity. Location informations are: name of the source file and line position in this file. They are found in the JDT ASTNode: ast. This method also creates some basic links between the entity and others (e.g. declaring container, return type, ...)
      Parameters:
